{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HiF9FWy4pNt89x26ttBcXK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the info I need:\n- The deployment has labels `app: demo-app`\n- It serves on port 5678\n- The path is `/` but we need to expose it at `/svc`\n\nI need to create:\n1. A Service that targets port 5678 with selector `app: demo-app`\n2. An Ingress with the nginx ingress class that routes `app.example.com/svc` to the service\n\nThe tricky part here is that the app only serves `/` but we need to expose it at `/svc`. I need to use the nginx `rewrite-target` annotation to rewrite `/svc` to `/`.\nI'll set up the rewrite annotation to transform the `/svc` path back to `/` for the backend, then create both the Service and Ingress resources.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":376,"cache_read_input_tokens":28721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":376},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa818fa1-7f73-404d-a6ff-5438764b90d3","uuid":"0acf065a-b6e0-48cd-986d-a6d89abbb814","request_id":"req_011Ccak13SSU3tmStPvg2pSg"}
